content:
Get Better Performance for List Views

To improve performance and meet the latest accessibility standards, list views for custom objects now render with Lightning Web Components (LWC) instead of Aura. LWC delivers your data faster and makes the latest features available for your list views.

The List Views dropdown menu displays up to 100 lists and shows Recent List Views and the option to search your lists at the top of the dropdown. Keyboard navigation starts with focus at the top of the list rather than on the currently pinned list.

Some icons and highlights have updated colors, and the color, size, alignment, and capitalization of some windows, buttons, and dropdown menus have changed.

The Filters panel has new button options in the add or edit filters work flows. Cancel to exit the add or edit filter flow, and Save to apply your changes. 

When you add or edit a filter, the Value menu closes each time you select an option from it. Options appear below the Value menu as you select them.

When you create a filter that uses a location-based field, the values initially show as the full location name in the Filters panel. After saving, the values convert to an abbreviated form.

After adding or editing a filter, keyboard focus returns to the Add Filter button or edited filter.

Header icons in columns and fields donâ€™t render.
Some errors and in-app messages appear in updated locations or formats and with new language.
title: Improved List Views Performance
